
            
                1 Is unemployment a great problem where you live now?Do you know people who have lost their jobs recently?
            
                2  What do you think  the role of the government is in regulating the unemployment situation in this country? How should the government help people who have lost their jobs?
            
                3 Describe an employe whom the employer will never fire.
            
                4 When is the best time for a person to start looking for a job? Is it better to start job hunting while you are still studying and try to combine your studies with work? Can you share your experiences.
            
                5 Can youremember what was your very first job?  Can you tell us about it?
            
                6 Do you think that at universities students get enough knowledge and practice to have no difficulties when starting to work for some company. What should young people do to have enough qualification after graduation?
            
                7 What are the most efficient ways to look for a job? Friends? The Internet? Newspapers?
            
                8 How do you behave at a job interview to produce a favorable impression on the employer?
            
                9 Do you feel nervous or relaxed and confident at job interviews? Share your experiences.
            
                10 What are some questions you have been asked in an interview? Have you ever been asked some questions which seemed really strange and funny to you?
            
                11 Have you ever been cheated by the employer?  What can you do to protect yourself?
